  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Not Accepted — Discretization error below required level)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 6 factors assessed and meeting required levels, 1 factor assessed but failing to meet required level (Discretization error: required 3, achieved 2), 6 factors scoped-out with documented rationale. Decision: Not accepted pending remediation of mesh independence study.",
